        <title>Activity: To recognise, describe and use [LO 1.12.1]</title>
        <para id="id20368916">As with multiplication, there are particular rules for division by multiples of 10, that enable you to calculate answers in a flash – without using pencil and paper! You have to form groups of three learners for the following activity.</para>
        <para id="id20441827">1. See if you can formulate rules for the following:</para>
        <para id="id19871221">2. Division by 10: __________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id20337144">_______________________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id20368266">_______________________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id20360144">3. Division by 100: _________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id14464815">_______________________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id14464820">_______________________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id20635331">4. Division by 1 000: ________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id19595411">_______________________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id20404514">_______________________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id20404519">5. Division by 10 000: _______________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id14610496">_______________________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id20433240">_______________________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id7234431">6. Compare your answers with those of the class!</para>
        <para id="id4941821">7. How quickly can YOU write down the answers to the following without using a calculator?</para>
